   activation.                                                                  
 • Cancer: Various types, including leukemia and carcinoma, are discussed in    
   relation to cytokine interactions.                                           
 • Infectious Diseases: Conditions like hepatitis and tuberculosis are explored 
   for their cytokine profiles.                                                 

                                 Gene Symbols:                                  

 • IL6: Interleukin-6, a key cytokine in inflammation and immune responses.     
 • TNF: Tumor necrosis factor, involved in inflammation and immune regulation.  
 • IFNG: Interferon-gamma, important for immune cell activation and antiviral   
   responses.                                                                   
 • IL1B: Interleukin-1 beta, a pro-inflammatory cytokine.                       
 • CSF2: Colony-stimulating factor 2, involved in hematopoiesis and immune cell 
   function.                                                                    

